Q: Upper Bound
Question Link: https://takeuforward.org/arrays/implement-upper-bound
Question Explanation: Given a sorted array and you need to figure out the smallest index such that it should be greater than x. i.e., arr[ind] > x

Approach: Here in this problem, first visualize the scenario such that where will be the answer in the array, is it will be on left side or right size of the mid. 

T.C: 0(logN) and S.C: O(1)

Code:

class UpperBoundFinder {
    // Binary search to find upper bound
    public int upperBound(int[] arr, int x) {
        int low = 0, high = arr.length - 1;
        int ans = arr.length;  // Default to length if not found

        while (low <= high) {
            int mid = (low + high) / 2;

            if (arr[mid] > x) {
                ans = mid;        // Store current index as potential answer
                high = mid - 1;   // Move left
            } else {
                low = mid + 1;    // Move right
            }
        }
        return ans;  // Return final answer
    }
